<p><b>ABAP</b> (Advanced Business Application Programming, originally <i>Allgemeiner Berichts-Aufbereitungs-Prozessor</i>, German for "general report creation processor"<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup>) is a <a href="/wiki/High-level_programming_language" title="High-level programming language">high-level programming language</a> created by the German <a href="/wiki/Software" title="Software">software</a> company <a href="/wiki/SAP_SE" title="SAP SE">SAP SE</a>. It is currently positioned, alongside <a href="/wiki/Java_(programming_language)" title="Java (programming language)">Java</a>, as the language for programming the <a href="/wiki/SAP_Web_Application_Server" class="mw-redirect" title="SAP Web Application Server">SAP Application Server</a>, which is part of the <a href="/wiki/NetWeaver" class="mw-redirect" title="NetWeaver">NetWeaver</a> platform for building business applications.</p>
<p></p>
